## Remarks

`ColorExtensions` adds conversion methods to <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor>, <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColor>, and <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColorF> so that colors can be round-tripped between HarfBuzz and SkiaSharp. Channel values are clamped to the 0–255 range when converting from `SKColorF`.

## Examples

```csharp
// Convert an SKColor to HBColor and back
SKColor skColor = SKColors.Red;
HBColor hbColor = skColor.ToHBColor();
SKColor roundTripped = hbColor.ToSKColor();
```
